annotation.TEXT: At least the game provided a 1-up there, as if it knew this situation was likely. (Or, it's just being generous in general as usual.)
Okay, now I can helicopter across. Flandre will likewise also have to suicide now.
Oh, and this can obviously be used as a life-farming spot. Hehehe...
Oh, and by perfect run, I mean no-death run, because no-damage is clearly impossible.
This looks like a stage designed for Marisa... Let's go back right away.
Well, I guess we should charge through the spike wall on the right, since left is just a dead end right now.
This looks like a stage designed for Alice. I should step back.
This is a stage for Nitori, I see. I have nothing to do here.
Well, at least the game provides F items for both of us. Oh, wait...
We need to hit the red switch to the left of the starting point, and that'll require tanking two hits. So, that's why there were two F items. Oops.
After that, you're not forced to take any more hits in this room, so the P in the spike ball cage here is totally unnecessary if things are going perfectly.
Alright, and there's the goal, along with 24 more 1-ups! (As if we hadn't gained enough lives from repeatedly collecting the 8 near the previous checkpoint!)
This is a stage for Nitori. I'm going back.
This seems like a stage designed for Alice. I should go back.
Oh, and as a result of that last forced hit, it's impossible to complete this level with full health, as far as I can tell. Anyway, there you go-- a no-death run of 6-4!
Yep, this is gonna be a thing alright. (This is already reminding me of the brutal bonus level of Cave Story.) I think we're gonna need some fitting music here...
Now we just gotta do the jump correctly.
This is a stage designed for Alice. I wouldn't be able to proceed.
Use Extending Arm here to grab the book, then carefully time your double-jump to get through the red spikes below.
This looks like a stage for Patchouli. It's impossible for me.
First of all, only take one F at a time here. So, grab the first F, hit the red switch below, eating a couple hits along the way, then come back for the second F.
This looks like a stage designed for Marisa. Let's go back to the select screen.
That one was my fault, for not allowing the camera to go down for Flandre there.
Wow... That sure was a thing! And I'm thankful that we sort of lucked into the book (and that there were no DCs)! Now for my perfect run...
Wait, do we want that yellow switch ON? Because that would block off the door.
Aha! We managed to respawn-abuse our way past that hurdle!
In fact, we're gonna gain several lives every time we fail even without abusing the pause menu! Well, I guess it's about time I brought Yakety Sax back...
I like to intentionally take a hit from the first pair of fairies there, as it's much easier than dealing with them the intended way, and there's an F just afterwards.
This is a stage for Patchouli. I can't do anything with my extending arm!
There's a P that can be grabbed with the Extending Arm.
...Yeah, I think we have to ram our way through the spikes to get out of here.
Okay, our teamwork there did work (though that wasn't the best way to cheese the puzzle).
Hello, and welcome back to Urapani! This time, we'll be playing 6-4, which will star our resident kappa, Nitori!
Of course, the demo counts will remain up there since we're still dying left and right.
(Note: I recorded this before doing my successful no-death run of 6-4, in case you're wondering why I'm back to 731 lives and 12 points.)
Well, we saw the door that time. Let's hope that really is the goal door.
Okay, now we have a race situation. We have to activate this timer switch, run back and turn the yellow switch OFF, then get past the green timer gate in front of the door before it resolidifies.
This looks like a stage designed for Marisa. Let's go back!
At this point, eat a hit from the gray spikes, then immediately grab the F and go through all of the gray spikes while still invincible, as you need full HP to have enough energy for the next part.
Oh, that was interesting what I did there. If only I didn't hesitate over that red spike ball.
D'oh, Flandre, you didn't have to follow me. Only one of us needed to come down here to hit the switch. Now we're both gonna be reduced to 1 HP.
Okay, time for the final leg...
And, thanks to all those 1-ups, Game Over is pretty much impossible here! (I just pray Flandre doesn't DC now...)
I can go down here, carefully stomp these vanilla FOEs without hitting the chocolate one or jumping back into the cage, and then hit the blue switch.
This looks like a stage for Patchouli. Maybe I should take a nap.
Now, I had absolutely zero failures in the first half of the level. Once you know what to do, it's pretty easy.
Is there something I'm not seeing here, or is the game going to make us take forced hits to get out of this cage?
Also, you have a decent amount of leeway with the timer switch here. You can fall to the floor below after hitting it, and still make it in time.
Geez, we've been at this for a while... But, the fact that I've stopped the Yakety Sax music now should mean something...
Oh, we're actually making progress here, finally. I wish Flandre hadn't gobbled up that last F so hastily, though.
Bah, I missed the switch. And, we weren't gonna make it anyway. (Also, I overlooked the possibility that this could easily have been cheesed with 2 players.)
Hey, maybe I can abuse my respawn invincibility here.
This is a stage for me! I'll do my best!
And now, I'll leave you with footage of me revisiting each of the world 6 levels to check what the first message of each level says with the wrong characters. To be continued... Ze!
Pretty easy to helicopter through here.
The helicopter is obviously needed here, so we'll have to suicide and respawn to make it across now.
Okay, now for the second half, where all of my failures were. BTW, each time I failed, I practiced the part I failed on multiple times before starting over for another real attempt.
This is a stage for Nitori. Looks troublesome, so better leave it to her.
Oh, geez... What are we in for now? I'd better just leave our demo counts fully visible continuously here.

However, that last pair of fairies must be dealt with flawlessly, as you need full HP upon reaching the cracked blocks, because then you need to tank 1 more hit, but still be able to use Extending Arm to hit a switch afterwards.
Holy crackers! That was some epic respawn timing for Flandre there! And, even better, here's a checkpoint, so the book is secure!
...Oh. We need the switch ON so we can land on those blocks. Fortunately, the floor down here is possible to escape from without dying.
